race.comment: BLAZING GURU (2) returned after a seven-week absence and was having his first run for the new stable when a respectable sixth in the Cowra Cup over 1700m last start. Raced once over this trip and was successful. Big drop in class today and the return to a staying journey should see him right in the finish. MIDNIGHT AFFAIR (7) settled towards the rear and was very one-paced over 1650m at Moruya last time. Has never raced beyond 1800m in her 27-start career but it looks the right option now. TAVIJEWEL (9) is racing well including an even effort to finish third over 2200m at Dubbo last Monday. Will be strong through the line when others might be raising the white flag. WILL TO EXCEL (1) and JOSHUA (11) both whacked away in the same race as TAVIJEWEL at Dubbo seven days ago, finishing fourth and fifth respectively. Dour stayers who should be thereabouts again.
